In a large frying pan or wok, heat the groundnut oil over a medium high heat.Add the chicken strips and cook, lightly tossing, for 3-4 minutes until the chicken turns white and is almost cooked through.Add the garlic, ginger, star anise and chilli, and cook for a further 30 seconds.Add the mangetout, pak choi, spring onions and mushrooms, and stir fry for another 3-4 minutes until they are all lightly cooked.Finish with the soy sauce, balsamic vinegar and fresh herbs. Stir together briefly and serve immediately.